   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Flooding Emergency Response in Chipinge (Start Fund 577)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&quot;1) Provision of potable water to 5 communities in the two (2) Wards were water points were affected = individuals
2) Provision of Tents and Polythene ropes to 85 vulnerable households
3) Hygiene kit distribution to 85 vulnerable households (soap, chlorine tab, jeri-cans)
4) Provision of cooking utensils to 15 households (pots, spoons, plates, cups)
Provision of  potable water: Provision storage tanks (5,000 litres of water storage tanks) to increase access and provide storage in key strategic places. Further to this, open wells will be disinfected and water tested to ensure the water is free from any disease. Hyper-chlorination of all water supplies through provision of chlorine tablets will be carried out. Providing Shelter:  Distribute tents and Polythen ropes to 85 households. NFIs Distribution:  Distribution of soap,sanitary ware, face masks, tents, kitchen utensils, and jeri-cans to 85 vulnerable HHs - which include HHs without incomes, the elderly, large familes, people with disabilities, HHs with young children, amongst other vulnerable groups.  Provision of PSS: The action will include provision of psychosocial support through group counselling carried out by community based PSychosocial Support (CBPSS) groups. Safegu</narrative>
  </description>
